title: For Sale/Trade:  1974 Marlin 336 "Texan" 30/30
postcontent: For trade/sale is a 1974, JM-stamped, Marlin 336 "Texan", chambered in 30-30. Overall, the rifle is in good condition, but it is visibly used, but functions flawlessly and all internals are very clean and unworn. Like most of these classic lever guns, it obviously hasn't had many rounds through it.  Other than a patch of thinning bluing on the top of barrel, the blued finish is very nice, but the stock looks like it spent a little time in the sun in a truck's gun rack. It isn't trashed or anything, so I never felt it warranted going to the trouble of doing a refinish job (and I actually like refinishing gun stocks). You can see the yellowing and worn spots in the varnish in the 2nd photo, that's about the extent of it.I pulled the scope and rings off a while back, it's back to it's scope-less "natural state" now, and I've since dialed in the iron sights (and I'll still include the scope and see-thru rings).  I'm placing this at a $450 trade valuation, which is a great price for these uncommon "Texan" variants, with the straight stock and lever. Buyer must be legal to own firearms, and be a legal Georgia resident with valid ID. As always, I'll show my ga DL and carry permit. Prefer meeting just north of town at the Chevron on exit 19 (Mulberry Grove), or north Columbus around Williams rd/N veterans pkwy, on days I'm in town.If the ad is still up, I still have the rifle!! title: For Sale:  MA Compliant, Fixed Magazine AR style Rifle - New Manufacture
postcontent:
Massachusetts-compliant, fixed (non-detachable) 10-round magazine AR-style rifle, manufactured by MassReloading at our Littleton location.
These are NOT entry-level rifles, and are guaranteed to shoot better than 1 MOA groups.
Our rifles feature mil-spec upper receivers and forged billet lower receivers with permanently affixed 10-round magazines. 
The heart of any AR-style rifle is the Bolt Carrier Group (BCG), and for this, we made NO compromises.  Ours is a premium quality, Made-in-the-USA BCG that features a Carpenter 158 bolt (properly heat-treated and MPI tested), a chrome lined, 8620, M16-profile bolt carrier with a chrome lined gas key that features properly-staked Grade 8 bolts.
The next most important part of the rifle is the barrel.  We selected a 16” US-made match-grade,  1:8 heavy barrel with a Wylde chamber and carbine-length gas system.  The versatile 1:8 twist enables you to shoot 40gr to 77gr bullets, while the Wylde chamber and 11° target crown ensure top accuracy with either 5.56 or .223 ammo.
This rifle has a 15” Key-mod, free-float, full-length rail handguard.  Also included are two separate 3” Picatinny rail sections that you can use to mount whatever ridiculous accessories you think belong on an already perfect rifle.
The rifles feature black or OD green Magpul fixed carbine stocks, Magpul MOE grips, Trinity Force extended takedown pins (with a ring-pull rear pin), and YHM HD extended charging handle latches.  The magazine is stainless steel (not plastic).
Each rifle comes with a soft case.MassReloading is an 07 FFL (manufacturer) and appointment-only firearms dealer located in Littleton, MA.  Our rifles are built with the highest quality US-made components to ensure reliability and superb accuracy.
